can i mix and match my best sat scores lets say i score on section a on section b on section c on the first sat it doesn't matter which categories just an example let's say i am upset with my section c score of so i choose to retake the sat now what if i get a on section a on section b and on section c my second time great my c score is up but my b score is down can i mix and match from the two tests to give me the highest scores possible also can i avoid this by taking only section c when i go to retake the sat well to answer your first question yes and no the colleges to which you apply will probably use only the highest scores from each section however you don't have the right to report your total sat score as a sum of the highest section scores from multiple test dates on your resume or on your college application to answer your second question no you have to take the whole test each time SAT Test (student assessment) GED Jeopardy! The Princeton Review Doomsday argument Science Bowl English cricket team History of Test cricket (1884 to 1889) Grade (education) ELO rating system President (game) Appeal Match Game Advanced Placement Program Law School Admissions Test Martial art Extreme Programming History of Test cricket (1890 to 1900) Quizbowl PSAT/NMSQT Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 2005 English cricket season Archery at the 2004 Summer Olympics Graduate Record Examination Whose Line Is It Anyway? The Joker's Wild Test cricket Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Education in Romania CPU cache Ken Jennings Medical College Admission Test Sydney Riot of 1879 The Ashes National Certificate of Educational Achievement Adjoint functors Many-worlds interpretation Australia's Brainiest Kid Tennis Bangladeshi cricket team in Sri Lanka in 2005-06 Dominoes American and British English differences Game show The Apprentice 2 $ale of the Century Troms__ I.L. Canasta College admissions Bayesian inference W. G. G